<taxonomicName id="DDBE80D4620E9A969AB66ABE1C364843" LSID="063185B5-1D4C-5F97-A071-417681804580" authority="Steiner et al., 2018" authorityName="Steiner et al." authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Messor" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Messor mcarthuri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mcarthuri">Messor mcarthuri Steiner et al., 2018</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8A5008B95AA72448DF67E056D353F769" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AC8E808649DF837F3AD4FEC011B3913D" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="81DC200A03838347F714DB4410B3F88E" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New records: Southern Black Sea coast, Rezovo vill., 09.05.2009, 1 w., leg. ALG (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8F67028D12577B9E68B735C2A728D13F" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7727165" captionText="Figure 3. Messor mcarthuri, major lateral: specimen from Rezovo vill.; scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e83658.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/653853" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">3</figureCitation>
); Strandzha Mt., Malko Tarnovo, Propada loc., 27.05.2009, 1 w., leg. ALG; East Rhodopes: Zornitsa vill., 19.04.2012, 5 w., leg. ALG; Meden buk vill., 09.04.2013, 8 w., leg. ALG; Gorni Glavanak vill., 01.05.2016, 6 w., leg. ALG; Sakar Mt., Matochina vill., 03.05.2019, 2 w., leg. ALG; Dervent Heights, Golyam Dervent vill., 06.06.2021, 12 w., leg. ALG (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CAF4158F7C5D83977EE5D25AB56B798E" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7727169" captionText="Figure 4. Messor mcarthuri, major lateral: specimen from Golyam Dervent vill. with intermediate characters between M. mcarthuri and M. hellenius; scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e83658.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/653854" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">4</figureCitation>
). Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="FF86002915C11A8A0406F10A10F72733" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D8BF5ED5687EEED4166A8B3FA5876083" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="75B71EB8A1090DADCB27639FB6921345" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="013B37F2EF89F5CC1EE96CA4DF4F5D0D" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
First record for Bulgaria. This is a recently described member of the 
<taxonomicName id="081B66471E2BB656C9E6BFBB9FE4FB7A" baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1798" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Messor" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Messor structor" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="structor">
<emphasis id="D2AFC2947464BCEA716F4AD74AABF34F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Messor structor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group (
<bibRefCitation id="0F4824E55A1520F36CA5636CC76A8D4F" author="Steiner, F. M." journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="387 - 404" refId="B7726040" refString="Steiner, F. M., Csosz, S., Marko, B., Gamisch, A., Rinnhofer, L., Folterbauer, C., Hammerle, S., Stauffer, C., Arthofer, W., Schlick-Steiner, B. C., 2018. Turning one into five: Integrative taxonomy uncovers complex evolution of cryptic species in the harvester ant Messor &quot; Messor structor &quot;. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 127: 387 - 404" title="Turning one into five: Integrative taxonomy uncovers complex evolution of cryptic species in the harvester ant Messor &quot; Messor structor &quot;" volume="127" year="2018">Steiner et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
), distributed in Greece and Turkey (
<bibRefCitation id="395A685E12B4FC23FE819B98136B39BD" author="Kiran, K." journalOrPublisher="Zoosystema" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="285 - 329" refId="B7725795" refString="Kiran, K., Karaman, C., 2020. Additions to the ant fauna of Turkey (Hymenoptera, Formicidae). Zoosystema 42 (18): 285 - 329" title="Additions to the ant fauna of Turkey (Hymenoptera, Formicidae)" volume="42" year="2020">Kiran and Karaman 2020</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="3932C55AD124FE5D7356A7B327EE4D12" author="Borowiec, L." journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Upper Silesian Museum in Bytom Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 33" refId="B7725678" refString="Borowiec, L., Wieczorek, K., Salata, S., 2021. Review of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of the Dodecanese Archipelago, Greece. Annals of the Upper Silesian Museum in Bytom Entomology 30: 1 - 33" title="Review of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of the Dodecanese Archipelago, Greece" volume="30" year="2021">Borowiec et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Specimens from the vicinity of the Meden buk and Golyam Dervent villages have intermediate characteristics between 
<taxonomicName id="26DA1CFC187FB0E47FF41F220CD8984A" genus="M." lsidName="M. mcarthuri" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="mcarthuri">
<emphasis id="8D42547FC6A4CFBBC498A1B83F8E8268" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">M. mcarthuri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="69B2A7699ABF172BDA780A74D053910E" genus="M." lsidName="M. hellenius" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="hellenius">
<emphasis id="73AA9B7EA2116D0BFB108392E6A6542D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">M. hellenius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which may indicate a possible hybridisation between these species (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E87AA6134483CD738E5C127392DAB865" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7727169" captionText="Figure 4. Messor mcarthuri, major lateral: specimen from Golyam Dervent vill. with intermediate characters between M. mcarthuri and M. hellenius; scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e83658.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/653854" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
